summary: This is a court subpoena issued by the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York to the School District of Palm Beach County. It commands the production of student enrollment records from Survivors Charter School for a specific student, as part of the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Named as the defendant in the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell, which is the matter for which the subpoena is issued.

events.title: Subpoena Compliance Date
events.description: The School District of Palm Beach County is commanded to appear and produce requested student enrollment records at the United States District Court.

locations: United States District Court for the Southern District of New York, 40 Foley Square, Borough of Manhattan, City of New York, New York
Survivors Charter School, West Palm Beach, Florida
School District of Palm Beach County
keyFacts: The subpoena is part of the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)).
It demands student enrollment records from Survivors Charter School in West Palm Beach, Florida, for a specific, unnamed student.
The subpoena was issued on July 6, 2021, with a compliance date set for November 29, 2021.
Failure to comply constitutes contempt of court and subjects the recipient to civil sanctions and criminal penalties.
